  "text": "More recently, the NADEEF [CITATION_1] tool has been developed in order to create a unified framework able to merge the most used cleansing solutions by both academy and industry. In our opinion, NADEEF gives an important contribution to data cleansing also providing an exhaustive overview about the most recent (and efficient) solutions for cleansing data. Indeed, as the authors remark, consistency requirements are usually defined on either a single tuple, two tuples or a set of tuples. The first two classes are enough for covering a wide spectrum of basic data quality requirements for which FD-based approaches are well-suited. However, the latter class of quality constraints (that NADEEF does not take into account according to its authors) requires reasoning with a (finite but not bounded) set of data items over time as the case of longitudinal data, and this makes the exploration-based technique a good candidate for that task.",
